en_889144_0	A sudden wildfire that broke out in and around Poonagala area in Haputale was brought to the notice of the troops in the Security Force Headquarters - Central on Thursday (8) morning.
en_889144_1	The fire broke out, due to prevailing drought spell and dry weather patterns was worsened with gushing winds that prevailed overnight.
en_889144_2	Troops managed to douse the wildfire within a couple of hours.
en_889144_3	More than 18 troops took part in the operation on the instructions of Major General Laksiri Waduge, Commander Security Forces - Central.
